==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[solein]]'', from Anglo-Norman ''solein'' ("[[alone]]"), from ''[[sol]]'' ("[[single]]"), from Latin [[sōlus]] ("by oneself alone").

===Pronunciation===
[[w:AHD|AHD]]: sŭl ' ən

===Adjective===
'''sullen''' ({{compar}}: [[sullener]], {{superl}}: [[sullenest]])

# having a brooding ill [[temper]]; [[sulky]].
# [[dismal]]; [[somber]].
# [[sluggish]]; [[slow]].

